        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Colombia elects new divided Congress ahead of May presidential vote Americas Issued on: 09/03/2026 - 15:01 In Colombia's congressional elections, preliminary results show President Gustavo Petro's left wing block has come out on top in the senate with the right wing Democratic Center party, founded by former President Álvaro Uribe edging ahead in the House of Representatives. Voters had to fill 102 Senate seats and 182 House seats, as well as choosing presidential candidates from the major parties in a primary style vote, ahead of presidential elections in May. Trump convenes regional leaders to curb crime, immigration 07/03/2026 Americas REPLAY: US hosts \"Shield of the Americas summit\" 07/03/2026 Americas Polymarket faces allegations of insider trading after suspicious Iran war bets 06/03/2026 Americas Iran war divides US Congress over Constitution interpretation 06/03/2026 Americas 'Purely defensive' posture: Europe’s reluctant role in an expanding Middle East conflict 06/03/2026 Middle East Trump fires controversial Homeland Security secretary Kristi Noem 06/03/2026 Americas US Congress rejects 'war powers resolution' that would halt strikes in Iran 06/03/2026 Middle East Donald Trump seeks Kyiv's help in defending against Iranian drones 06/03/2026 Middle East 'There doesn't seem to be a plan in Iran' for the Trump administation 06/03/2026 Middle East"
